message.content:
A washer is a small, circular, flat disc typically made of metal or rubber. 
It is used to distribute the load of a threaded fastener such as a bolt or nut. 
Washers may have a smooth or rough texture and edges with rounded or flat shapes. 
They come in a variety of sizes and thicknesses to fit specific applications. 
Washers are commonly used in plumbing, automotive, and construction industries. 
They can be found in hardware stores, tool shops, and online retailers. 
Visual characteristics of washers include their metallic or solid color, reflective surface, and varying texture depending on the material.
